Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles. When boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{2} and cook for ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{}. Meanwhile, cut the @lime{1} into quarters. Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly.

Heat drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the @beef sizzler steaks{4} and cook for ~{45%seconds} each side, until golden brown.

> IMPORTANT: The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Transfer the steaks to a #plate{} to rest but don't wash up the pan!

Return the pan to high heat, add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and, once hot, add the @baby corn, greens & carrots{200%g}. Stir fry for ~{2%minutes} then add the @hoisin sauce{50%g} and @soy sauce{25%g} with the cooked noodles and cook until everything is heated through, ~{1%minute}. Cut the steaks into 2cm wide pieces.

Divide the noodles and vegetables between plates. Top with the sliced steak and top with the sliced spring onion and @cashew pieces{25%g} and serve with lime wedges. Tear over the @coriander{1} and enjoy!